cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Permit-to-Proof in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "Permit-to-Proof: a verifiable LLM system for environmental-permit compliance extraction"
abstract: >-
  Permit-to-Proof extracts compliance obligations from environmental permits
  with a large language model and verifies every obligation against the source
  text with a separate, deterministic, domain-aware verification layer before
  it is trusted. It measures the error-detection lift the verification layer
  adds over a raw LLM, calibrates per-obligation confidence, and quantifies the
  resulting automation-versus-human-review trade-off.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Patil
    given-names: Kedar R.
    affiliation: "University of the Cumberlands"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - hallucination detection
  - source grounding
  - confidence calibration
  - environmental compliance
  - regulatory obligation extraction
  - human-in-the-loop
license: MIT
